The paper deals with problems in neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses label bias, which is a common issue in machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) likely categories as well. The paper uses neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses optimization techniques, which are commonly used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category.
